  "text": "Some recent ICN projects adopt flat, self-certifying, labels to name content. Initially employed in DONA's design [CITATION_1] , flat names are used by the route-by-name protocol (devised on top of the IP layer) to request content. Similarly, efforts by Dannewitz et al [CITATION_2] and Wong et al [CITATION_3] explore secure naming schemes to ensure the data is persistent and not accessed by unauthorized users.",
